# Hushly RAG Chatbot

An AI-powered knowledge base assistant for the Hushly SaaS platform. Built with a full RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) pipeline — scrapes, chunks, embeds, retrieves, and answers — with a Flask REST API and an LLM-as-judge evaluation harness.

-----

## What It Does

- Answers questions about Hushly’s product features using a curated knowledge base
- Uses **parent-child chunking** for precise retrieval with full context
- Rewrites follow-up questions using conversation history for better search accuracy
- Falls back from **Gemini → Groq (Llama)** automatically if one hits a rate limit
- Evaluates answer quality using an LLM judge scoring Faithfulness and Relevance

-----

## Architecture

```
User Query
    │
    ▼
Query Rewriter (Groq / Llama) ── uses last 3 turns of history
    │
    ▼
FAISS Vector Search ── sentence-transformers (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)
    │
    ▼
Parent-Child Retrieval ── child chunk matched, parent chunk used as context
    │
    ▼
LLM Answer Generation ── Gemini 2.0 Flash (fallback: Groq Llama)
    │
    ▼
Response + Sources
```

-----

## Project Structure

```
rag-project/
├── app.py               # Flask REST API (main server)
├── rag.py               # Standalone CLI version of the RAG pipeline
├── script.py            # Data ingestion: PDF → scrape URLs → chunk → save JSON
├── eval_rag.py          # LLM-as-judge evaluation harness
├── run_graphify.py      # Code architecture visualizer (graphifyy)
├── prompt.txt           # System prompt template for the LLM
├── chunks_enterprise.json  # Chunked knowledge base (generated by script.py)
├── faiss_index.bin      # FAISS vector index (auto-generated on first run)
├── faiss_texts.pkl      # Index metadata (auto-generated on first run)
├── kb.pdf               # Source knowledge base PDF
├── kb.html              # Frontend chat UI
├── requirements.txt     # Python dependencies
└── Procfile             # Deployment config (Heroku / Railway)
```

-----

## Setup

### 1. Clone the repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/sankeerthchelley/rag-project.git
cd rag-project
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Create a `.env` file

```env
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here
```

> **Free API keys:**
> 
> - Gemini: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
> - Groq: https://console.groq.com/keys

### 4. Build the knowledge base (first time only)

```bash
python script.py
```

This scrapes URLs from `kb.pdf`, chunks the content, and saves to `chunks_enterprise.json`.

### 5. Start the server

```bash
python app.py
```

Open `http://localhost:8000` in your browser.

> The FAISS index is built automatically on the first run and cached to disk for fast restarts.

-----

## API Endpoints

|Method|Endpoint         |Description                                     |
|------|-----------------|------------------------------------------------|
|`GET` |`/`              |Serves the chat UI                              |
|`GET` |`/health`        |Server status + index stats                     |
|`POST`|`/ask`           |Ask a question (supports conversation history)  |
|`POST`|`/enhance`       |Expand/clarify a short user query               |
|`POST`|`/generate_steps`|Convert an answer into step-by-step instructions|

### Example `/ask` Request

```json
POST /ask
{
  "query": "How do I upload an asset to Hushly?",
  "history": [
    { "role": "user", "content": "What are Hushly Experiences?" },
    { "role": "assistant", "content": "Experiences are personalized content pages..." }
  ]
}
```

### Example Response

```json
{
  "answer": "To upload an asset: 1. Go to Content in the left menu...",
  "model_used": "gemini",
  "no_info": false,
  "sources": ["https://hushly.freshdesk.com/..."],
  "titles": ["Uploading Assets"]
}
```

-----

## Running Evaluations

```bash
python eval_rag.py
```

Scores the pipeline on 7 test questions using an LLM judge (Gemini or Groq). Results saved to `rag_eval_results.json`.

**Metrics:**

- **Faithfulness** — Is the answer grounded in the retrieved context? (1–5)
- **Relevance** — Does the answer address the question? (1–5)

-----

## Tech Stack

|Component     |Technology                                |
|--------------|------------------------------------------|
|Embeddings    |`sentence-transformers` (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)|
|Vector Store  |FAISS                                     |
|Primary LLM   |Google Gemini 2.0 Flash                   |
|Fallback LLM  |Groq (Llama 3.1 / 3.3)                    |
|Web Framework |Flask                                     |
|Data Ingestion|LangChain, BeautifulSoup, PyPDFLoader     |
|Deployment    |Heroku / Railway (via Procfile)           |

-----

## Environment Variables

|Variable        |Description             |
|----------------|------------------------|
|`GEMINI_API_KEY`|Google AI Studio API key|
|`GROQ_API_KEY`  |Groq Cloud API key      |

-----

## Notes

- `faiss_index.bin` and `faiss_texts.pkl` are auto-generated — do not edit manually
- The system prompt lives in `prompt.txt` and is hot-reloaded on every request (no restart needed to update it)
- If Gemini hits a quota limit, the system automatically falls back to Groq
- Responses starting with `[NO_INFO]` trigger a Freshdesk search redirect in the UI